data.meta_description:
7,155 likes, 132 comments - mitchellandness on February 14, 2024: "The smoothest handles in the game…

Upon his arrival to New York in the 2004-05 NBA season, @JamalCrawford averaged 17.7 points and 4.3 assists per game, proving he was a great fit in NY.

In a game against the Miami Heat in 2007, Crawford made 16 consecutive shots on his way to a career-high 52 points and a Knicks victory.

Now introducing the Jamal Crawford 2004-05 New York Knicks Swingman Jersey.

#NBA #HardwoodClassics #JamalCrawford #Knicks".
